<section class="faq">
  <h3 class="title">FAQ</h3>
  <h3>How does a TwitterChat work?</h3>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>The moderators (Saron and Carlos) will post a question</strong>, like this one: "Q1: What are you favorite programming books? #CodeNewbie"</li>

    <li>You <strong>respond to the question</strong>, like this: "A1: I loved Chris Pine's 'Learn to Program.' Great book!#CodeNewbie"</li>

    <li><strong>Respond to people directly</strong>, like this: "@codergal what did you like about 'Learn to Program'? I've heard a lot about it! #CodeNewbie"</li>

    <li>After some discussion, roughly 5-10 minutes worth, <strong>Saron and Carlos will post a new question</strong> for the community to respond to.</li>

  </ul>

  <h3>How do I join the chat?</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Follow the hashtag #CodeNewbie<strong> every Wednesday at 7PM EST</strong>, and start tweeting with us!</li>

    <li>Respond to one of the questions, labeled <strong>"Q1", "Q2", "Q3"</strong>, etc, with a labeled answer <strong>"A1", "A2", "A3"</strong> etc.</li>

    <li>Respond to other people's tweets. <strong>Share a link. Tell a story. </strong>Talk about your coding experiences related to the topic.</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="signature">--- Be sure to include the #CodeNewbie hashtag ---</h2>

